            "summary": "Peach Coconut Ice Cream takes about <b>45 minutes</b> from beginning to end. For <b>72 cents per serving</b>, you get a dessert that serves 14. One portion of this dish contains around <b>2g of protein</b>, <b>14g of fat</b>, and a total of <b>190 calories</b>. Head to the store and pick up full-fat coconut milk, half & half, cane sugar, and a few other things to make it today. It is perfect for <b>Summer</b>. 8 people have made this recipe and would make it again. It is brought to you by Foodista. It is a good option if you're following a <b>gluten free and lacto ovo vegetarian</b> diet. Taking all factors into account, this recipe <b>earns a spoonacular score of 31%</b>, which is rather bad. Try <a href=\"https://spoonacular.com/recipes/coconut-peach-cobbler-with-bourbon-pecan-ice-cream-283506\">Coconut-Peach Cobbler with Bourbon-Pecan Ice Cream</a>, <a href=\"https://spoonacular.com/recipes/coconut-peach-ice-cream-with-toasted-almonds-best-lick-2008-54039\">Coconut Peach Ice Cream With Toasted Almonds Best Lick! 2008</a>, and <a href=\"https://spoonacular.com/recipes/roasted-strawberry-coconut-milk-ice-cream-vegan-tips-for-making-your-homemade-ice-cream-soft-814136\">Roasted Strawberry Coconut Milk Ice Cream (Vegan) + Tips for Making Your Homemade Ice Cream Soft</a> for similar recipes.",
